# ============================================================
# T2 Mac packages (2018–2020 Intel models)
# ============================================================
# The T2 security chip controls keyboard, trackpad, audio,
# and storage on these Macs. Without apple-bce, none of
# these work. The T2 packages come from the t2linux.org
# community repository.
# ============================================================

# --- T2 Core Driver ---
# NOTE: apple-bce-dkms is installed from the t2linux repo
# which is added during the inject-drivers.sh step.
# This file documents the intent; actual install is handled
# by the inject script which adds the apt repository first.

# Packages to install from t2linux repo:
# apple-bce-dkms        — keyboard, trackpad, audio, SSD
# apple-t2-audio-config — PipeWire/PulseAudio routing for T2
# apple-touchbar-dkms   — Touch Bar support (if applicable)

# --- Additional T2 support ---
mesa-utils

